td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   crafted</span><hr size=1> I am wondering when I can start this quest.  I hear a lot of the times the items needed just rot on the mobs becuase they are lore and only warriors want them, other times I hear you can find em on vendors.  I am level 18 btw and constantly group with an 18 chanter.  Should I try to get a hih level friend to just trn in the stuff and give it to me? All help is appreiciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/01 6:27:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> Aviak charm (gauntlets) - found in SK of aviaks lvl 28-30s. shout for this, you can usually get one free. I offered 20pp and got 1 in minutes.<br>
<br>
Optic nerves (bracers) - i got a good deal on bracers, but I understand that many vendors in the EK, Gorge, Runny-eye are will have these on them.<br>
<br>
Eye of Griffon (vambraces) - in NK and EK off griffs. Shout for this, druids kite em all the time. Got ine free.<br>
<br>
Dark Circlet (greaves) - in Najena, will probably take a group of 20s to get this. Since zone is not very populated, you will probably have to do this yourself.<br>
<br>
Fire totem (helm) - Depending on your servers, Sol A might be a popular zone. If it is, zone in and shout for it. If not, take a group.<br>
<br>
Rune of dorfs (pauldron) - Runny eye should be popular now since patch. Evil Eyes are probably not being camped though. Still some question as to whether EE is gorge will drop these now too. Anyway, a group should do fine in Runnyeye.<br>
<br>
Frost Toem (Boots) - go during a Vox raid. Higher levels can waste the gobbies, you get free totem.<br>
<br>
Werewolf Talon (bp) - this one is tough. If you can get some friends to help, it will be no problem, but it will probably take a few friends. I have seem sheer numbers take down solo 50s. If you get luck and have a high level group there, you should be able to get one from them.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
 <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 45th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 22 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ulanolwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lanolwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/01 7:24:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thanks</span><hr size=1> Thank you, I will try this, now all I need is the 1500pp for the gems. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umintzyfresch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mintzy Fresch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/3/01 9:37:16 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/uryvichk/mintzy.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> Speaking of which, is there anywhere you can get the gems you need *dropped*? I wanted to quest for Crafted myself, to *save* money... but geez, the costs for those gems is bank-breaking to say the least. Any magic happy place full of ruby-dropping mobs around that we can get to in the 20s-40s?<br>
<br>
-Mintzy Fresch,<br>
Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 9:33:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> Bad news on gem dropps. While there is a chance that some mabs will drop gems, by the time you see enough of the quest gems drop, you will have made many thousands of pp just hunting and selling loot.<br>
<br>
The good news is that if you do these quests at the appropriate level, not only will you be getting exp from all of the mobs you will have to kill, but you should be able to come up with the plats needed for the gems while questing for the component. Keep in mind that 1500pp for gems covers 9 pieces of armor. That an average price of less than 200pp each piece. Plus you can sell the piece of armor you are replacing for a few plats.<br>
<br>
Get the quest pieces and the plats for the gems will come. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 45th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 22 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umintzyfresch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mintzy Fresch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 7:11:10 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/uryvichk/mintzy.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> Right, I just want to know where the mobs that even drop the gems *are*... of course, knowing where I can get 100s of pp in loot wouldn't hurt either, pickings so far have been slim. Then too, if I didn't have to drop so much to stay under weight limits, I might have a fair bit more cash than I do now.<br>
<br>
-Mintzy Fresch,<br>
Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugigantus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gigantus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/9/01 5:04:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> Many mobs drop various gems as randoms. By the time you get mobs dropping rubies you might as well go to Hate or Growth and get some nodrop armor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unailened.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nailened</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/9/01 7:32:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> Hehe.  Unfortunately, it's all too true.  Was hunting in Sebilis last night and got rubies and fire opals and fire emeralds.  Hehe.  That's a 50+ zone easy.  So, go hunt , kill , sell , hunt , kill , sell and you'll get the cash ya need to get your gems.  What can help is if you can find an enchanter or bard (high cha) to purchase the gems for you.  That will save you some cash.  Good luck!  <br>
<br>
Lomax Loatheheart<br>
54th Dwarven Champion<br>
Hope's Beginning<br>
Vazaelle<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gangleri>Gangleri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/9/01 10:29:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> Well from my own experience, I went directly from banded to Crafted. I guess I got my first piece of Crafted in the very high 20ies and had the full suit (except the pauldrons) by 34 or 35...<br>
 Just play and save yer pp look for deals on it. you can sometimes find it for only slightly more than cost of stones..At least for me with my 40 Charisma.<br>
 Also, the Dark Circlet needed from Najena is very easy to get, Can solo  get it in low 30ies and a group in  low mid twenties I'm sure...<br>
 The helm is'nt to bad either ... A goblin shaman that drops the totem spawns in the room beside the drunk's room alot...<br>
  Also, like others said the items needed go to waste alot. go to the drop zones and ask nice if you can loot it. I'm sure no one will mind. Im sure some will even help ya .<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usinark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinark</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/01 6:57:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: crafted</span><hr size=1> As far as old world mobs go, seafuries in OOT are a great source of gems. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showMessage?topicID=115.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showMessage?topicID=113.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=107.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.threadControl?topicID=107.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=107.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=107.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table b